<Paragraph> You can lock the structure of a workbook, which prevents users from adding or deleting worksheets or from displaying hidden worksheets. You can also prevent users from changing the size or position of worksheet windows. Workbook structure and window protection apply to the entire workbook.</Paragraph>
<Paragraph> To protect a workbook, point to <Bold>Protection</Bold> on the <Bold>Tools</Bold> menu, and then click <Bold>Protect Workbook</Bold>. You can choose which elements you want to protect (workbook structure, windows, or both) by selecting or clearing the corresponding check boxes.</Paragraph>
<Paragraph> Below is an image showing workbook protection in Microsoft Excel.</Paragraph>

<Paragraph TextAlignment ="Center">
 <Image Source="Images\WorkbookProtection_ProtectedWorkbook.png" Stretch="None" /> 
</Paragraph>

